import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

from datetime import datetime

# Calculate patient age
today = pd.Timestamp(''now'')

    ''BillingAmount'': ''mean'',
    ''Age'': ''mean''
}).reset_index()

# Rename for clarity
agg.rename(columns={
    ''DurationMinutes'': ''AvgDuration'',
    ''BillingAmount'': ''AvgBilling'',

}, inplace=True)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.stats import zscore

df = dataset.copy()
df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()
df[''TestDate''] = pd.to_datetime(df[''TestDate''], errors=''coerce'')
df = df.dropna(subset=[''TestDate'', ''TestType''])

# Daily test count
df[''TestDate''] = df[''TestDate''].dt.date
daily_counts = df.groupby([''TestDate'', ''TestType'']).size().reset_index(name=''TestCount'')

# Z-score to detect spikes
daily_counts[''ZScore''] = daily_counts.groupby(''TestType'')[''TestCount''].transform(lambda x: zscore(x, ddof=0))
daily_counts[''Anomaly''] = daily_counts[''ZScore''].abs() > 2.5

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
for test_type in daily_counts[''TestType''].unique():
    temp = daily_counts[daily_counts[''TestType''] == test_type]
    plt.plot(temp[''TestDate''], temp[''TestCount''], label=f"{test_type}", alpha=0.5)
    spikes = temp[temp[''Anomaly'']]
    plt.scatter(spikes[''TestDate''], spikes[''TestCount''], color=''red'', label=f"Spike: {test_type}")

plt.legend()
plt.title("Diagnostic Test Load Anomalies")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Test Volume")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()'"}}},"provider":{"expr":{"Literal":{"Value":"'Python'"}}}}}]}}}
